  schema:name "Strawberry spinach cultivation" ;
  schema:description "Growing protocol for *Chenopodium capitatum*, dual-harvest crop producing spinach-like leaves in juvenile phase (20–35 days) then edible red berries after bolting. Hardy annual to zone 2; self-seeds aggressively. Minimal pest pressure; excellent permaculture crop. Both leaves and berries edible; flavor improves after frost." ;
